VMs = Software emulations of physical computers

Represent IaaS - Don't have to maintain hardware

Provides:
	- Total control over OS
	- Run Customer Software
	- Development and Testing environment
	- Extend DCs

Available in different sizes




	- Azure managed disks are block-level storage with volumes that are managed by Azure
	- Managed disks are similar to physical disks in an on-prem environment, but virtualized. 
	- With managed disks, you only need to specify the disk size, and Azure will provision automatically


IOPS = Input/output operations per second
